properties.title: Puerto Rio Tranquilo
Leaving Villa o Higgins
properties.description: Travel along a winding road departing from the remote town of Villa O'Higgins, surrounded by untouched Patagonian wilderness. The journey offers dramatic landscapes with rugged mountains and pristine valleys.

properties.title: Taking the ferry.
properties.description: Board the ferry to cross scenic waterways. The tranquil ferry ride provides stunning views of the surrounding fjords and glacial landscapes, a unique way to experience the heart of Patagonia.

properties.title: Long ride to Cochrane
properties.description: A long but rewarding stretch through the breathtaking Chilean wilderness. This segment features rolling hills, dense forests, and panoramic views of distant mountains as you approach the charming town of Cochrane.

properties.title: Towards Puerto Bertrand
properties.description: Travel through an enchanting landscape of crystal-clear rivers and lush greenery. This section guides you toward the vibrant blue waters of Puerto Bertrand, a beautiful lake region surrounded by impressive natural scenery.

properties.title: On the blue shores
properties.description: A scenic journey along the shimmering blue shores of glacial lakes. This segment features gentle curves and spectacular vistas, with serene waters reflecting the towering peaks and rugged terrain.

properties.title: The Explorers Valley
properties.description: A journey to the majestic Valle de Exploradores
